cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the distributed control of a set of mobile robots, which is a typical problem in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS). Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and protocols to control the robots, which falls under the scope of cs.RO (Robotics). The concept of Lyndon words is used to design the protocol, which is related to the field of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the analysis and proof of the protocol's correctness, which is related to the field of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical concepts and techniques to analyze the protocol's performance, which is related to the field of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
